      "type": "text",
      "description": "Photosynthesis is the process by which plants produce energy."
    },
    {
      "id": "point1",
      "type": "text",
      "description": "It primarily occurs in plant leaves and uses sunlight to transform water and carbon dioxide into glucose, a sugar molecule that serves as food for plants."
    },
    {
      "id": "point2",
      "type": "text",
      "description": "Oxygen is produced as a byproduct of photosynthesis during this conversion process."
    },
    {
      "id": "point3",
      "type": "text",
      "description": "Chlorophyll, the green pigment in chloroplasts, captures sunlight and initiates the photosynthetic reaction known as the light-dependent reactions."
    }
